position.title: Software Engineering Intern
position.description:
I worked with a team of engineers to develop an internal scalable data pipeline for Adobe Analytics that aims to simplify the process of gathering and cleaning data for Adobe data scientists. Throughout my internship, I have successfully developed four main tools: 

1. Variable Utilization Project
* Worked with a team of three engineers to design the architecture of, and implement, a scalable data pipeline that automatically updates and maintains Adobe Analytics data for internal analysis (SQL, Sequalize, Adobe Analytics API, Node.js)
* Created a virtualized UI that enables users to view, edit, map, and analyze Adobe Analytics data (Aurelia, Node.js)

2. Data Sampling Tool
* Created an API for sampling data from Adobe Analytics (Aurelia API). Use Case - pulling data from Adobe Analytics could take hours or even days, depending on the size of the request, so I've created a sampling functionality that runs in several seconds and fetches a sample of the data pull request for approval before initiating the full data pull request
* Designed and implemented the data sampling UI

3. Time Estimation Model
* Designed and implemented a data pull request time estimation model for the Adobe Analytics API with an average error of 15 mins
* The model used a random forest regressor along with several extracted features to estimate how much time the data pull request will take

4. Developed a secure internal email notifications system (SMTP) that has voluntarily been activated by almost all the users

position.title: Co-Founder and Lead Software Engineer
position.description:
Website: www.tamerny.com

What's Tamerny?

Tamerny is a text-based platform that centralizes the on-demand market. Users can text the Tamerny phone number anything they would like to purchase or any service they would like to have and we will get it for them, it's an automated assistant service that operates in the middle east.

"Anything, one text away"

What have I worked on?

- Developed a web application on Meteor
- Designed the platform using Materialize
- Integrated Moyasar, Careem, and several other API's to the platform
- Developed the SMS text distribution system and the Operator Functionality Dashboard
- Recruited four members to design, tech, and finance
- Pitched to investors and raised seed funding
- Conducted market research
- Held Alpha and beta testing sessions

position.title: Co-Founder and Software Engineer
position.description:
What is Empaninst?

Empanist is Startup that came out of the Harvard Venture Incubator Program which aims to digitalize the collaborative music making industry by connecting musicians and accompanists together.

What have I worked on?

- Developed both the front-end and back-end segments of the platform using Javascript and node.js
- Collaboratively designed the platform using Materialize
- Implemented data visualizations using D3
- Constructed a business plan and revenue model
- Conducted Alpha and Beta testing sessions

Platform complexity and structure:

The platform that we developed was very similar in structure to the LinkedIn and AirBnb platforms. Users were able to search for each other, fill in resume profiles, and book/pay for sessions.

items.title: CS181: Classifying Malicious Software (1st place winner, accuracy rate: 93.5%)
items.description: Worked with a team of three to design and implement a boosting classification algorithm that detects and labels 12 critical viruses. Our implementation extracted the md5 hash of an executable file, retrieved further information on the hash from the VirusTotal API, and finally vectorized and labeled the executable with a single viruses type

items.title: Crypto Exchange Network Fee Reduction Through TTC
items.description: In this project, we examined how to reduce cryptocurrency transaction fees through TTC. To motivate, why this is important, it is important to understand that one of the key benefits that cryptocurrencies were constructed to have in comparison to traditional fiat currencies is the ability to transfer money at a lower cost in comparison to traditional financial institutions.

items.title: Al Zibdah
items.description:
We are consuming too much noise from the internet. Wasting hours of valuable time on junk media. Thereâ€™s a lack of useful content on the internet that is both easy to parse/understand and fun to consume at the same time. Al Zibdah is an iOS/Android application that aids the creation and spread of simple, fun, and useful content online.

I have participated in the Tech Entrepreneurship Sprint in Prince Mohammed Bin Salman College with Al Zibdah and won 2nd place. After the competition, I formed a small founding team around Al Zibdah that is working on developing the product, doing market research, and finally launching it.

items.title: Electro Bag
items.description:
Electro Bag is a recycling trashcan that automatically separates plastics, metals, and papers from each other and places them in separate containers. It uses barcode scanning and a density estimation system to analyze objects placed inside it to guess what they are made of and place them in the correct bin.

This is the project that got me interested in computer science and electrical engineering in the first place!
